Reproducible analysis scripts for tinydenseR
=============================================

These scripts reproduce the analyses presented in the tinydenseR manuscript.
All scripts are self-contained in terms of working directory detection and
output folder creation.  Run via `Rscript --file=<script>` or source from
RStudio.

Requirements: R >= 4.1, tinydenseR (this package), plus script-specific
packages listed at the top of each file.


## Self-contained simulation scripts (no external data needed)

sim_flow_DA.R               Simulated differential abundance (flow cytometry)
                            with tinydenseR. Three effect sizes (0.5%, 5%, 50%).
                            Includes exact stratified permutation testing.

sim_flow_DE.R               Simulated differential expression (flow cytometry)
                            with tinydenseR. Three effect sizes (0.5SD, 1SD, 2SD).
                            Includes exact stratified permutation testing.

sim_flow_DA_diffcyt.R       Same simulated DA data analysed with diffcyt
                            (FlowSOM + edgeR). Comparator method.

sim_flow_DE_diffcyt.R       Same simulated DE data analysed with diffcyt
                            (FlowSOM + limma). Comparator method.

sim_scRNAseq_trajectory_tdr.R
                            Simulated scRNA-seq trajectory analysis with
                            tinydenseR.  Uses package-shipped data
                            (sim_trajectory_tdr). Includes permutation testing.


## Scripts requiring external data (user must supply input files)

benchmark_methods_comparison.R
                            Benchmark tinydenseR, Seurat, and miloR on the
                            COVID PBMC dataset. Measures time and memory at
                            multiple cell-count levels. Edit DATA_DIR at the
                            top of the script.

head_to_head_Seu.R          Head-to-head comparison of Seurat vs tinydenseR
                            cell type composition on COVID PBMC data.
                            Requires a pre-processed Seurat v5 object
                            (see comments in script for creation instructions).

landmark_integration.R      Landmark-level vs cell-level Harmony integration
                            comparison on Luecken et al. Immune_ALL_human
                            benchmark dataset (33,506 cells, 10 batches).
                            Downloads from: https://figshare.com/ndownloader/files/25717328


## Utility scripts (sourced by other scripts, not run standalone)

perm_utils.R                Exact stratified permutation test functions and
                            plotting utilities.  Sourced by sim_flow_DA.R,
                            sim_flow_DE.R, and sim_scRNAseq_trajectory_tdr.R.

peak_mem_profvis.R          Extracts peak memory and elapsed time from profvis
                            profile objects.  Sourced by
                            benchmark_methods_comparison.R.